        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 22 at 5:17PM MDT until June 22 at 6:00PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>SVRABQ

The National Weather Service in Albuquerque has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Central Curry County in east central New Mexico...
Southeastern Quay County in east central New Mexico...

* Until 600 PM MDT.

* At 517 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
8 miles east of Quay to near Saint Vrain, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and small hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Clovis, San Jon, Grady, Wheatland, Broadview, Ranchvale, Saint
Vrain and Forrest.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 348 and 356.
Highway 60 between Mile Markers 367 and 377.
</description>
        <instruction>Seek shelter inside a well-built structure and stay away from
windows. These storms are capable of producing damaging winds.</instruction>
